    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "Hey, I need help writing a rejection email. We had a candidate, Marcus, who made it all the way to the final interview for our Senior Dev role here in Austin. He's really talented and had great technical skills, but we decided to go with someone who had a bit more experience with our specific cloud architecture. I want the email to be professional and kind because he was a great guy, but we need to be firm that the decision is final. Can you draft something?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Subject: Your Application for Senior Dev Role at [Your Company Name]\n\nDear Marcus,\n\nI hope this message finds you well. After careful consideration and thorough evaluation, I regret to inform you that we have decided to move forward with another candidate for the Senior Dev position at [Your Company Name].\n\nWe were impressed by your skills, experience, and enthusiasm during the interview process, and we wish you the best in your future endeavors. The decision was challenging given your qualifications, but ultimately, we felt that your experience with our specific cloud architecture was slightly more aligned with our current needs.\n\nThank you once again for taking the time to apply and for the interest you showed in our company. We appreciate your understanding and wish you continued success in your career.\n\nBest regards,\n\n[Your Name]\n[Your Job Title]\n[Your Company Name]\n[Your Contact Information]",
